Class Generation

  • java.lang.Object
    • logic.Generation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Integer>, DynamicWorld
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GenerationConcurrHash, GenerationHash

    public abstract class Generation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Integer>, DynamicWorld
    A Generation is a representation of living cells at a point in time. This Generation superclass contains the methods for converting an index to integer, and vice versa. Generation implements Iterable to enable the enhanced for-loop in the DynamicBoard's draw-method.
    The abstract methods are restrictions every subclass needs to implement.
    We have created two subclasses:
    GenerationHash - A HashMap representation
    GenerationConcurrHash - A ConcurrentHashMap representation that uses threads for better performance
